title: Fleet Foxes - "Wading In Waist-High Water" (Solstice Version)

media:group.media:title: Fleet Foxes - "Wading In Waist-High Water" (Solstice Version)
media:group.media:description:
"Wading In Waist-High Water" (Solstice Version) by @Fleet Foxes from the album 'A Very Lonely Solstice', available now
Stream & download: https://fleetfoxes.ffm.to/averylonelysolstice

Available for the first time since 2020's Winter Solstice Recording at Brooklyn's St. Ann & The Holy Trinity Church. Watch The Full Performance: https://youtu.be/3VB24LYsE60

Lyrics

Summer all over
Blame it on timing
Weakening August water
Loose-eyed in morning
Sunlight covered over
Wading in sight of fire

And we're finally aligning
More than maybe I can choose

Soon as I knew you
All so wide open
Wading inside of fire
As if I just saw you
Cross Second Avenue
Wading in waist-high water

And I love you so violent
More than maybe I can do

Now we're finally aligning
More than maybe I can choose
